## 4. Realtime notifications (Socket.IO)

Server event flow: `NewNotificationEvent` -> save in DB -> emit `notification.received`.

```typescript
import { io, Socket } from 'socket.io-client';

export interface NotificationSubscribePayload {
  userId: string;
}

export interface NotificationReceivedPayload extends NotificationItem {}

export function getSocketUrl(): string {
  const apiUrl = import.meta.env.VITE_API_URL ?? 'http://localhost:8080/api';
  try {
    return new URL(apiUrl).origin;
  } catch {
    return 'http://localhost:8080';
  }
}

export function connectNotificationsSocket(): Socket {
  return io(getSocketUrl(), {
    path: '/socket.io',
    transports: ['websocket', 'polling'],
  });
}
```

Subscribe/listen:

```typescript
const socket = connectNotificationsSocket();
socket.emit('subscribe', { userId: currentUser.id } satisfies NotificationSubscribePayload);

socket.on('notification.received', (payload: NotificationReceivedPayload) => {
  // prepend to list, increment badge, show toast
  console.log('notification.received', payload);
});
```

---

## 5. Suggested UI functions

- `fetchInitialNotifications()` -> call `GET /notifications` on page load
- `loadMoreNotifications()` -> increment `offset` pagination
- `markAsReadLocal(id)` -> optimistic local state update (until backend endpoint exists)
- `bindRealtimeNotifications(userId)` -> subscribe socket + return cleanup

---

## 6. Quick reference

| Method | Path | Auth | Purpose |
|---|---|---|---|
| `POST` | `/api/notifications` | JWT | create notification |
| `GET` | `/api/notifications` | JWT | list my notifications |
| `GET` | `/api/notifications/:id` | JWT | get one notification |
| WS emit | `subscribe` | socket | subscribe user room |
| WS on | `notification.received` | socket | receive realtime notification |

---

## 7. Important note

Current websocket subscription uses `userId` from client payload.  
For production hardening, prefer socket auth (JWT/session) and derive user ID server-side.
